WEBVTT

00:00.898 --> 00:01.479
Brilliant.

00:01.960 --> 00:02.501
Thank you.

00:02.602 --> 00:05.708
Everyone who has read, I have to say I'm impressed with all the Christmas outfits.

00:06.269 --> 00:10.037
And thank you so much for leading us so beautifully today.

00:11.260 --> 00:12.141
My name's Nicola.

00:12.161 --> 00:12.502
Hello.

00:12.522 --> 00:20.178
And I get just for a little bit, just to pull together some of what we've sung about.

00:20.802 --> 00:28.253
One of the most powerful lines in the Carol Hark, the herald angels sing, which we're going to sing to finish today shortly.

00:28.774 --> 00:36.265
There's a line, and it's speaking of Jesus, and it says, light and life to all he brings.

00:37.787 --> 00:50.386
And in a world that can so often feel dark, heavy, and confusing, Christmas reminds us that Jesus, God's own son, came to bring life

00:50.690 --> 00:52.572
and light and hope.

00:53.253 --> 00:56.336
So I just want to pull out three short things.

00:56.837 --> 00:59.900
One is this idea of light in the darkness.

01:01.502 --> 01:06.047
The world that Jesus entered over 2000 years ago wasn't peaceful.

01:06.828 --> 01:08.110
It wasn't easy.

01:08.130 --> 01:09.972
It was troubled.

01:10.432 --> 01:12.975
It was divided and it was weary.

01:12.995 --> 01:19.282
You just have to watch the news to see some very similar issues today.

01:19.874 --> 01:23.419
And for some, Christmas is a beautiful season.

01:24.321 --> 01:34.917
But for others, especially those who are walking through loneliness, through bereavement, through significant change, this time of year can be particularly hard.

01:35.117 --> 01:39.584
And I know some, even in this room, I'm missing someone they love dearly.

01:40.726 --> 01:46.354
Some maybe in this room might be surrounded by people and yet feel very much alone.

01:47.394 --> 01:52.761
some may be carrying burdens of various kinds, some really worried about world events.

01:54.063 --> 02:05.719
But into the sense of darkness that can accompany all of these things, the Bible declares, the light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.

02:06.600 --> 02:09.804
See, Jesus is not intimidated by darkness.

02:10.265 --> 02:11.186
He stepped

02:11.330 --> 02:12.371
right into it.

02:12.831 --> 02:25.784
And just as he did 2000 and so years ago, he steps towards you today and he offers his presence, his light in your darkness and he offers his hope.

02:26.745 --> 02:29.368
And you might ask, okay, how?

02:29.568 --> 02:30.329
What does that mean?

02:30.369 --> 02:32.211
How is that even possible?

02:32.891 --> 02:39.698
Well, the second thing I want to talk briefly about is this baby Jesus who came to save.

02:40.514 --> 02:51.272
See, at the heart of the Christmas story is this tiny newborn baby boy laying in a manger, fully God and fully human.

02:52.494 --> 02:59.826
And you know, he didn't come to add a holiday onto our calendars, but to begin a rescue mission.

03:01.026 --> 03:12.286
The angel of the Lord said to Joseph in a dream, Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary home as your wife because what is conceived in her is from the Holy Spirit.

03:12.306 --> 03:15.151
She'll give birth to a son and you ought to give him the name.

03:15.652 --> 03:16.633
Joseph, listen up.

03:16.954 --> 03:23.686
You ought to give him the name Jesus because he will save his people from their sins.

03:24.627 --> 03:26.130
This rescue mission,

03:26.466 --> 03:33.915
didn't look like anyone had really expected, in spite of all of the prophecies that we heard just one of this morning.

03:34.396 --> 03:37.380
But Jesus came as a baby into this world.

03:37.960 --> 03:48.794
And the world we all experience, the world we know, the troubles we experience, he came into that, into our world, the world that we know.

03:48.834 --> 03:52.018
And all of us know what that kind of

03:52.418 --> 03:54.060
Darkness can feel like.

03:54.160 --> 03:55.462
It might feel like fear.

03:55.522 --> 03:57.084
It might feel like guilt.

03:57.505 --> 04:01.550
It might feel like confusion or simply being far from God.

04:02.591 --> 04:09.740
And the Bible says we experience that kind of darkness because we were created for a relationship with God.

04:10.381 --> 04:13.685
But we've all turned from Him in our own ways.

04:14.046 --> 04:17.190
And that separation is what the Bible calls sin.

04:17.630 --> 04:20.434
And it's that sin that separates us from God.

04:20.706 --> 04:31.117
And that's the darkness, really, that the Scriptures speak of, that sin that separates us from God over and over, wider and wider.

04:31.717 --> 04:37.063
And we are unable to save ourselves from that darkness and put it right.

04:37.503 --> 04:40.446
We are unable to bring light to our lives.

04:40.867 --> 04:42.428
And that's why we need a Savior.

04:42.709 --> 04:45.031
That's why we need a rescuer.

04:45.872 --> 04:47.794
And the amazing news is

04:47.970 --> 04:52.638
The birth of Jesus was the start of this divine rescue mission.

04:52.718 --> 04:54.581
He came to save us.

04:55.222 --> 04:56.545
He came to us.

04:56.665 --> 05:08.165
He came to our lives, not far off and distant, looking on from the outside as some may be perceived God to be, but in human form, he came to us.

05:09.808 --> 05:13.554
Understanding our struggles, knowing our sin,

05:14.178 --> 05:18.705
And because he is God, this is the amazing thing that he is able to rescue us.

05:19.065 --> 05:29.821
He's able to carry our burdens, including grief, including pain, and including loneliness, including our fears, including all of our anxieties.

05:30.142 --> 05:35.690
He's able to do that as well as rescue us from our sin.

05:37.433 --> 05:43.762
But by his life, by his death, and then his miraculous resurrection,

05:44.866 --> 05:45.767
Just think about that.

05:46.388 --> 05:49.552
Sin and rebellion has a price to pay.

05:49.592 --> 05:53.858
You know, if I commit a crime this afternoon, I would expect to be punished.

05:54.459 --> 05:55.841
I'm not planning to, but you know.

05:56.141 --> 06:00.547
But it's true, if we commit a crime, there is punishment that is due to us.

06:02.089 --> 06:08.818
Well, the light and the life that Jesus offers us, the good news, the gift that we saw about on that video at the start,

06:09.058 --> 06:12.383
is that because Jesus lived his sinless life.

06:12.643 --> 06:21.858
He lived in this world like us, but he didn't sin like we do, not even in his thoughts, not at all, not one, not even an incy-wincey one, none.

06:21.878 --> 06:29.790
And yet when he died on the cross, he did it to bear the punishment that we all deserved.

06:31.032 --> 06:33.095
He paid the ultimate price.

06:33.155 --> 06:34.817
God sent his son.

06:34.857 --> 06:37.842
He died for our sin.

06:38.402 --> 06:44.451
He died for our rebellion and he died for our sin.

06:44.491 --> 06:58.050
And he proved his power over that sin, over that death, over that darkness, over that separation by taking all of our sin to the grave.

06:58.551 --> 07:00.854
And on the third day he rose again.

07:00.874 --> 07:06.162
He alone has the power to be our rescuer, to raise from the dead.

07:06.594 --> 07:10.921
overcoming the power of sin, overcoming the power of darkness.

07:13.306 --> 07:14.207
Isn't that amazing?

07:14.407 --> 07:17.693
That is what Christmas is about, this baby who came to save.

07:18.414 --> 07:27.530
And thirdly, that light and life is for you, for you, for you, this Christmas.

07:28.792 --> 07:32.178
Because of his perfect and sinless life,

07:32.674 --> 07:40.766
His death and his resurrection, he is able, he alone is able to offer you light and life.

07:42.048 --> 07:46.936
And he says to us, he says things like, I know the things that trouble you.

07:47.296 --> 07:49.980
I know the ways that you have wandered from me.

07:50.862 --> 07:56.210
But he describes himself as being like a shepherd who tends a flock.

07:57.154 --> 08:01.881
who comes looking, who knows each one of us with great care.

08:01.981 --> 08:04.685
He comes with this gift of a rescue.

08:07.169 --> 08:17.844
He comes with this gift of his perfect life, exchange for your sin, exchange for my sin and my rebellion.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.409
His life paid the price.

08:21.590 --> 08:24.594
His life took the punishment for my sin.

08:25.154 --> 08:27.738
and for your sin and for your rebellion.

08:29.260 --> 08:37.391
And because he did that, he has opened up a way for all to receive forgiveness and new life.

08:38.553 --> 08:42.077
This is the light and life that we've been singing about.

08:42.698 --> 08:54.034
And as a really famous verse, sometimes see it even at football matches, for God so loved the world that he gave his one and only son, that whoever

08:54.210 --> 08:59.296
believes in him, shall not perish, but have eternal life.

08:59.757 --> 09:04.102
John 3, 16, whoever believed.

09:05.404 --> 09:09.349
He came to save the whole world into the darkness of the night.

09:09.369 --> 09:16.958
This baby was born, this light broke in full of grace for you, for you.

09:16.978 --> 09:19.541
This is personal, this Christmas.

09:19.982 --> 09:23.506
The most epic story in the whole of history

09:25.154 --> 09:25.835
is for you.

09:28.818 --> 09:31.380
So here it is in a nutshell.

09:33.542 --> 09:42.631
All of us know what darkness feels like, fear, guilt, brokenness, confusion, or simply just feeling far from God.

09:43.832 --> 09:53.842
And the Bible says, we experienced this because we were created for relationship with God, but we've all turned from Him.

09:54.562 --> 09:57.025
And that separation is sin.

09:57.085 --> 09:58.907
That's what the Bible calls sin.

09:59.988 --> 10:02.490
But God did not leave us in the dark.

10:03.311 --> 10:07.816
He sent Jesus, his son, into the world as the light.

10:08.677 --> 10:12.781
Jesus lived the life that we couldn't live without sin.

10:13.642 --> 10:19.568
And then willingly died on the cross to take the punishment for our sin that it deserved.

10:20.189 --> 10:21.330
And three days later,

10:21.570 --> 10:27.759
He rose from the dead, breaking the power of darkness forever, forever.

10:30.243 --> 10:39.476
And because of Jesus, everybody, absolutely everybody can be forgiven, made new, brought back into God's family.

10:39.817 --> 10:43.783
It isn't something we earn, it's something that we receive.

10:44.964 --> 10:46.887
It's a gift of grace.

10:47.668 --> 10:51.474
And it starts with turning to Jesus, turning from

10:51.554 --> 11:06.132
darkness to his light, trusting him as the only one who saves, and choosing to follow him with our lives and knowing him for all eternity.

11:06.953 --> 11:11.819
He's broken even the power of death as we understand it.

11:12.960 --> 11:13.661
What a promise.

11:14.342 --> 11:16.545
You know, what amazing good news.

11:17.346 --> 11:21.010
And at this Carol service, we want to say, you know,

11:21.122 --> 11:27.692
If you this morning are ready to call out to him now, then you can simply come to him.

11:28.373 --> 11:30.716
And if you're not used to praying, it's okay.

11:30.977 --> 11:32.459
It's part of my job to help you.

11:32.679 --> 11:35.363
And I am very, very excited to do that.

11:36.185 --> 11:37.126
So I'm going to pray.

11:37.867 --> 11:40.631
And I'm going to tell you actually what I'm going to say first.

11:40.651 --> 11:42.674
And then you can decide if you agree with that.

11:42.694 --> 11:44.096
And then we'll pray together.

11:44.477 --> 11:48.563
So this is the prayer which says, I've been going my way.

11:48.603 --> 11:50.546
I've been

11:51.778 --> 11:58.429
I've been living in darkness, I've been living in sin and selfishness and all of the things that you're not proud of.

11:58.449 --> 12:02.957
And actually this morning I realized for the first time that you have come.

12:03.218 --> 12:15.218
Christmas is about a gift of grace and I want to receive that and I want to turn from the way I have been living and receive your light and your life and live with you now for all eternity.

12:15.426 --> 12:17.409
So this is what I'm going to propose.

12:17.429 --> 12:18.390
I pray in a minute.

12:18.410 --> 12:23.497
I've written it down just so I make sure it's the same both times so no one can think I'm tricking anyone.

12:23.918 --> 12:26.141
So Jesus, I need you.

12:26.161 --> 12:28.724
I turn from my sin now.

12:28.764 --> 12:37.336
I'm sorry for the things that I've done and said in my life that have moved me further and further away from your goodness and your ways.

12:38.217 --> 12:44.626
I know you love me with a love that reaches me today in my darkness and I choose to trust you.

12:45.282 --> 12:47.124
Invite you today into my life.

12:48.546 --> 12:49.567
Be my savior.

12:49.607 --> 12:55.715
And lead me in your light now and for all my days.

12:56.896 --> 12:58.618
Okay?

12:58.638 --> 13:00.180
So, there we go.

13:00.220 --> 13:02.023
If you want to close your eyes, you can.

13:02.123 --> 13:04.225
If you want to keep your eyes open, you can.

13:05.186 --> 13:14.578
But I want to invite you, if you've never realized, if you've never known that this baby at Christmas is a rescue mission for you.

13:14.786 --> 13:22.136
God's divine epic plan, and that you have a choice to make, to follow Him, and you want to do that.

13:22.717 --> 13:23.357
Let's pray.

13:24.880 --> 13:26.822
Jesus, I need you.

13:29.546 --> 13:31.188
I turn from my sin now.

13:31.208 --> 13:44.626
I am sorry for the things I have done and said in my life that have moved me further and further from your goodness and from your ways.

13:47.234 --> 13:53.180
Jesus, I know that you love me with a love that reaches me today in my darkness.

13:53.941 --> 13:55.382
And I choose to trust you.

13:55.622 --> 13:59.806
I invite you today into my life.

14:01.047 --> 14:06.933
Be my savior and lead me in your light now and for all my days.

14:08.555 --> 14:10.817
Amen.

14:10.837 --> 14:16.082
And he promises that whoever comes to him, he will never push away.

14:16.642 --> 14:19.065
Jesus is light in the darkness.

14:19.486 --> 14:20.968
That never comes to an end.

14:21.909 --> 14:32.984
And as his dearly loved child, that's not only for here on earth, that's for all eternity in heaven today forever.

14:33.545 --> 14:38.392
So if you prayed that, we would love to, yeah, it's the beginning of a journey.

14:39.153 --> 14:46.002
You know, it's the beginning of a journey and we would love to talk with you to, yeah, to have a conversation.

14:46.146 --> 14:49.930
Paks here, new believers, paks have got a bit of information in them.

14:50.330 --> 14:52.972
We'd love to give you those as well.

14:53.013 --> 14:58.978
And if you'd like to continue exploring, there are always questions to ask.

14:59.258 --> 15:03.242
We've got a fantastic opportunity in 2026 early on.

15:03.783 --> 15:08.467
We'd be running a new alpha course, which you and your friends would be really, really welcome to.

15:08.507 --> 15:15.634
It's a relaxed space to just explore the Christian faith and ask any questions you've got.

15:15.746 --> 15:29.659
So if you are searching, if you're hurting, if you're curious, if you just want a place to have a free dinner and listen to others, Alpha might be a perfect next step and you really will be invited.

15:29.959 --> 15:33.282
No pressure, no cost, no agenda, just come.

15:34.684 --> 15:45.554
I want to just encourage you to let Christmas not just be a season that you pass through this year, but the beginning of a journey towards light and life

15:45.666 --> 15:46.327
and hope.

15:46.968 --> 15:53.060
And I'm going to give you a moment to just reflect on what I've said and maybe some things that have been read or sung already this morning.

15:53.340 --> 15:58.951
And the band are just going to sing a song over us to give us an opportunity to do that.

16:00.534 --> 16:00.594
OK.

21:06.082 --> 21:08.206
going to be drawing to an end in a moment.

21:08.286 --> 21:14.757
I've just, when I've been thinking about sin and this rescue mission, we went through a phase in our house.

21:14.817 --> 21:17.782
My kids went through a phase of watching Bondi Beach.

21:17.922 --> 21:19.024
Don't you ever seen it?

21:19.044 --> 21:23.031
It's about the life garden in Australia at Bondi Beach.

21:23.071 --> 21:31.986
And I kept thinking about, like, sin is sometimes like being caught in a rip current and you kind of pulled further and further from the shore.

21:32.066 --> 21:35.018
And these rescuers on Bondi Beach, they come.

21:35.039 --> 21:41.586
And just as we were worshipping before, I kind of saw someone who was pulled out in the rip current.

21:41.666 --> 21:46.972
And the guys came out with their boards and everything, and they had to just reach out their hands.

21:47.552 --> 21:51.837
And it might be that you're thinking, well, I don't know all the answers to all my questions.

21:52.317 --> 22:00.246
I don't know, but actually to be rescued is just as well to just reach out one hand, one finger if you can.

22:00.806 --> 22:01.707
And he is there.

22:01.908 --> 22:07.954
He will grab hold of you, and he will help you, and he will carry you and rescue you.

